---
// props-panel-stress — Chapter 049 Lesson 2, "The preview server loop".
//
// The "props panel is a live what-if" figure. The placeholder asked for a real
// screenshot of the React Email 6 preview UI with the `firstName` field mid-edit
// to a long value and the heading wrapping in the main panel. That UI is a
// third-party tool we can't capture here, so — exactly as the sibling
// PreviewDefaultState.astro does, and as the teaching-chapter convention
// requires — we build a faithful HTML/CSS MOCKUP of it inside the lesson's
// <Screenshot> frame instead of embedding a literal image.
//
// What the mock depicts, and why each piece is here:
//   - the same slim top chrome bar as the default-state figure (wordmark +
//     viewport/dark/Send glyphs), so the student recognizes it as the same tool;
//   - a left PROPS panel — the editable controls the server derives from
//     PreviewProps. The `firstName` field is shown mid-edit: it is the focused
//     control (accent ring + a blinking caret after the long value), holding
//     "Maximilian-Alexander". The `verifyUrl` field sits below it for context.
//     This is the half of the cause→effect the prose describes ("edit a field");
//   - a main render canvas showing the welcome email with the heading
//     "Welcome, Maximilian-Alexander!" visibly WRAPPING onto a second line and
//     pressing the column edge — the effect of that edit, the whole point.
//
// The template list from the default-state figure is intentionally dropped here:
// this figure's single job is the field→render causality, and the list would
// only add clutter (the student already saw it in the previous figure).
//
// Built as plain HTML+CSS (the diagrams index's pick for a UI illustration),
// wrapped in <Screenshot viewport="desktop"> inside <Figure> per the placeholder.
// An aria-label carries the prose the placeholder specified as <img> alt text,
// so the figure is described to assistive tech despite having no <img>.
// `.not-content` opts out of Starlight prose styling; Starlight CSS variables
// (with hard fallbacks) keep it themed on both the light and dark Figure card.

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';
import Screenshot from '../../../figures/screenshot/Screenshot.astro';

const ALT =
	'The React Email preview server props panel with the firstName field edited to the long name Maximilian-Alexander; in the main panel the rendered heading wraps onto a second line.';

// The long value being typed into firstName — the realistic stress case the
// prose names. Splitting it lets us style the trailing caret as a sibling.
const LONG_NAME = 'Maximilian-Alexander';
---

<Figure>
	<Screenshot viewport="desktop">
		<div class="rep not-content" role="img" aria-label={ALT}>
			<!-- Top chrome: same grammar as the default-state figure. -->
			<div class="rep-topbar">
				<span class="rep-brand">
					<span class="rep-brand-mark">◢◣</span>
					<span class="rep-brand-text">React Email</span>
				</span>
				<span class="rep-tools" aria-hidden="true">
					<span class="rep-tool">Desktop</span>
					<span class="rep-tool rep-tool-icon" title="Mobile viewport">▢</span>
					<span class="rep-tool rep-tool-icon" title="Dark mode">◑</span>
					<span class="rep-tool rep-tool-cta">Send</span>
				</span>
			</div>

			<div class="rep-body">
				<!-- Left panel: the editable controls derived from PreviewProps. -->
				<aside class="rep-props">
					<div class="rep-props-head">
						<span class="rep-props-label">PROPS</span>
					</div>

					<!-- firstName — the focused, mid-edit field holding the long value. -->
					<div class="rep-field is-focused">
						<label class="rep-field-key">firstName</label>
						<div class="rep-input is-active">
							<span class="rep-input-val">{LONG_NAME}</span><span
								class="rep-caret"
								aria-hidden="true"></span>
						</div>
					</div>

					<!-- verifyUrl — context, the other prop the server surfaced. -->
					<div class="rep-field">
						<label class="rep-field-key">verifyUrl</label>
						<div class="rep-input">
							<span class="rep-input-val rep-input-muted"
								>https://yourapp.com/verify/abc123</span
							>
						</div>
					</div>
				</aside>

				<!-- Main panel: the render reacting to the edit — heading wraps. -->
				<section class="rep-main">
					<div class="rep-main-bar" aria-hidden="true">
						<span class="rep-tabpill is-active">Preview</span>
						<span class="rep-tabpill">HTML</span>
						<span class="rep-tabpill">Plain Text</span>
					</div>
					<div class="rep-canvas">
						<div class="rep-email">
							<div class="rep-email-logo">YourApp</div>
							<!-- The heading is forced to wrap: the long name pushes the
							     greeting onto a second line, hard against the column edge. -->
							<h3 class="rep-email-h">Welcome, {LONG_NAME}!</h3>
							<p class="rep-email-p">
								Thanks for signing up. Confirm your address to activate your
								account and get started.
							</p>
							<span class="rep-email-btn">Verify email</span>
							<p class="rep-email-foot">
								If you didn’t create an account, you can ignore this email.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
	</Screenshot>
	<Fragment slot="caption">
		Editing <code>firstName</code> in the props panel re-renders instantly — a faster
		way to stress-test wrapping than re-running the real send path.
	</Fragment>
</Figure>

<style>
	/* ---- shell (shared grammar with PreviewDefaultState) ------------------- */
	.rep {
		margin: 0;
		font-family:
			ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		line-height: 1.5;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
	}

	/* ---- top chrome bar ---------------------------------------------------- */
	.rep-topbar {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 12px;
		padding: 9px 14px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #d0d5dd);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar, #f7f8fa);
	}
	.rep-brand {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.01em;
	}
	.rep-brand-mark {
		font-size: 11px;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
	}
	.rep-tools {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 7px;
	}
	.rep-tool {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		min-width: 22px;
		height: 22px;
		padding: 0 8px;
		border-radius: 6px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #d0d5dd);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
		font-size: 11.5px;
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	.rep-tool-icon {
		padding: 0;
	}
	.rep-tool-cta {
		border-color: transparent;
		background: var(--sl-color-text-accent, #4f46e5);
		color: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
	}

	/* ---- two-pane body ----------------------------------------------------- */
	.rep-body {
		display: flex;
		min-height: 320px;
	}

	/* ---- left props panel -------------------------------------------------- */
	.rep-props {
		flex: 0 0 40%;
		max-width: 248px;
		border-right: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #d0d5dd);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg-sidebar, #f7f8fa);
		padding: 12px 12px 14px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 14px;
	}
	.rep-props-head {
		padding: 0 0 2px;
	}
	.rep-props-label {
		font-size: 10.5px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
	}
	.rep-field {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 5px;
	}
	.rep-field-key {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
	}
	.rep-input {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		min-height: 30px;
		padding: 5px 9px;
		border-radius: 6px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #d0d5dd);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 12px;
		line-height: 1.4;
		overflow: hidden;
	}
	/* The focused, mid-edit field gets the accent ring the real UI shows. */
	.rep-input.is-active {
		border-color: var(--sl-color-text-accent, #4f46e5);
		box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px
			color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-text-accent, #4f46e5) 22%, transparent);
	}
	.rep-input-val {
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #0f172a);
		white-space: nowrap;
		overflow: hidden;
		text-overflow: ellipsis;
	}
	.rep-input-muted {
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
	}
	/* Blinking text caret right after the typed value, selling "mid-edit". */
	.rep-caret {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		width: 1.5px;
		height: 15px;
		margin-left: 1px;
		background: var(--sl-color-text-accent, #4f46e5);
		animation: rep-blink 1.05s step-end infinite;
	}
	@keyframes rep-blink {
		0%,
		50% {
			opacity: 1;
		}
		50.01%,
		100% {
			opacity: 0;
		}
	}
	@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
		.rep-caret {
			animation: none;
		}
	}

	/* ---- main panel -------------------------------------------------------- */
	.rep-main {
		flex: 1 1 auto;
		min-width: 0;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
	}
	.rep-main-bar {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 6px;
		padding: 8px 12px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #d0d5dd);
	}
	.rep-tabpill {
		padding: 3px 10px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-size: 11.5px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
	}
	.rep-tabpill.is-active {
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-5, #94a3b8) 35%, transparent);
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
	}

	/* The render stage — neutral backdrop the email card floats on. */
	.rep-canvas {
		flex: 1 1 auto;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
		padding: 22px 16px;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--sl-color-gray-5, #94a3b8) 12%, var(--sl-color-bg, #fff));
	}

	/* The rendered welcome email — a fixed-width column so the long name has to
	   wrap rather than widening the card. */
	.rep-email {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 340px;
		align-self: flex-start;
		box-sizing: border-box;
		padding: 26px 24px 22px;
		border-radius: 10px;
		background: #ffffff;
		border: 1px solid #e7e9ee;
		box-shadow: 0 1px 3px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
		text-align: center;
		color: #1e293b;
	}
	.rep-email-logo {
		font-weight: 800;
		font-size: 15px;
		letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		color: #4f46e5;
		margin: 0 0 18px;
	}
	.rep-email-h {
		margin: 0 0 10px;
		font-size: 21px;
		line-height: 1.25;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #0f172a;
		/* Let the hyphenated long name break and wrap inside the fixed column —
		   this is the failure mode the figure exists to show. */
		overflow-wrap: anywhere;
	}
	.rep-email-p {
		margin: 0 0 20px;
		font-size: 13.5px;
		line-height: 1.55;
		color: #475569;
	}
	.rep-email-btn {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 10px 22px;
		border-radius: 8px;
		background: #4f46e5;
		color: #ffffff;
		font-size: 13.5px;
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	.rep-email-foot {
		margin: 20px 0 0;
		font-size: 11.5px;
		line-height: 1.5;
		color: #94a3b8;
	}

	/* On a narrow Figure keep both panes legible: shrink the props panel rather
	   than letting the email card get squeezed. */
	@media (max-width: 520px) {
		.rep-props {
			flex-basis: 44%;
			max-width: 168px;
			padding: 10px 9px 12px;
		}
		.rep-canvas {
			padding: 16px 10px;
		}
	}
</style>
